📝 Step 1: Install Module

Go to Apps in Odoo (Developer Mode ON).

Search for Generic Read Only User Access.

Click Install.

✅ Now the module is active in your database.

📝 Step 2: Create Test User

Settings → Users & Companies → Users → Create

Name: Test Readonly

Login: testreadonly

Email: anything

Groups: Internal User only

Save user.

📝 Step 3: Assign Read Only

Open the user form. You will see 2 buttons (from the module):

👁 Readonly → Click this.
✅ readonly = True
✅ User added to group Read Only Access.

✏ Read/Write → Click to revert.
